The paper deals with the k nearest neighbors problem in the plane, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry and machine learning. The paper also discusses the development of a static data structure and a dynamic version for the general setting with nearly optimal space and query time. These topics are closely related to computational geometry (cs.CG), data structures (cs.DS), and machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves the analysis of geometric structures using a new random sampling technique, which is related to discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
